# Phase 20 — Cloudflare Production Readiness Review

## Objective

Produce a final production-readiness review framework covering all Cloudflare governance areas accumulated across Phases 10–19. This provides a comprehensive checklist, a go/no-go decision template, and a rollback readiness checklist that must be completed before any Cloudflare production change.

This phase must NOT deploy, apply, destroy, or mutate Cloudflare. It is a documentation and checklist layer only.

---

## Branch Name

```
fix/cloudflare-production-readiness-review
```

## Commit Message

```
docs(cloudflare): add production readiness review
```

---

## Scope

- Create production readiness review overview doc
- Create production readiness checklist with pass/fail/blocked fields per area
- Create go/no-go decision template
- Create rollback readiness checklist
- Update `docs/infra/cloudflare-drift-report.md` with readiness reference
- Update `infra/cloudflare/README.md` with Phase 20 entry

---

## Non-Goals

- Do NOT run `wrangler deploy`, `terraform apply`, `tofu apply`, or any Cloudflare write
- Do NOT print, log, or commit secrets, credentials, or tokens
- Do NOT start or restart any services
- Do NOT edit `/etc/cloudflared/config.yml`
- Do NOT modify files outside Phase 20 scope

---

## Safety Rules

1. All checklist items must have status fields: `[ ] PASS`, `[ ] FAIL`, `[ ] BLOCKED`, `[ ] N/A`
2. No step in the checklist should trigger an automated deployment or write
3. Live verification steps must be labeled `[READ-ONLY]` or `[MANUAL]`
4. All docs must clearly separate: governance area | status | evidence reference | owner | blocker description
5. Rollback checklist must reference Phase 13 (break-glass) and Phase 12 (rollback plan) evidence
6. Never print secrets or credentials in examples

